name: float_f32_one_plus_epsilon
description: |
  This is the binary32 value immediately above 1, exactly 1 + 2^-23. The pair
  differs by one unit in the last place, so it probes approximate-equality
  thresholds, lossy serialization, and displays that round both values to the
  same short decimal string.
format: hex
decode-as: f32
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f32"
  - "epsilon"
  - "ulp"
  - "precision"
---
01 00 80 3f   # 0x3f800001: 1.00000011920928955078125
